===Etymology===
From the English ''[[inflexion]]'', from the {{etyl|la}} ''[[inflexio]]'', ''[[inflexionis]]'' (''a bending away from''); the variant spelling ''[[inflection]]'' is due to influence from ''[[correction]]''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en-us-inflection.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# {{grammar}} a change in the form of a word that reflects a change in grammatical function.
# a change in [[pitch]] or [[tone]] of voice.
# {{context|mathematics}} a change in curvature from [[concave]] to [[convex]] or from convex to concave.
# a turning away from a straight course.

